<subSubSection id="607317B5C2EE0C5B42C26CCEE92D8497" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" type="type">
<paragraph id="7EE6DFB2DDA13034D8A8FFD5D7923BA7" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11AC7215BAFAAD703DEDEE7CC293B64F" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">
KAZAKHSTAN, 
<emphasis id="33A0B242B3AD341878D1E2F125AF791F" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Popov</emphasis>
546 (holotype LE!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FA049A29D7575472FFFD3FF4B77EFE5F" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" type="description">
<paragraph id="E40E82E1C4D56A1409EEDCB9F1DD5D9F" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9097D792EE7AF6FEE11D94C8D97023C3" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">
Sometimes treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="D602B6CC0796051109F560A7D0928BFF" authorityName="Turcz., Bull. Soc. Imp. Naturalistes Moscou 5: 201. 1832. (Turczaninow" authorityYear="1832" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus tragacanthoides" order="Solanales" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tragacanthoides">
<emphasis id="EF31C4EF0FAA52FE5339D8D46026EB93" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convolvulus tragacanthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this species appears to be distinct. It is less obviously a cushion plant having stems to at least 30 cm in height, but commonly 5-10 cm, the branches all spinescent even when young; leaves linear to oblanceolate, 0.2-0.6 cm wide; flowers subsessile in clusters of 1-5 at the apex of the stem, often with a solitary pedunculate flower borne on a rigid, woody peduncle below the apical cluster; peduncles on axillary flowers 4-13 mm; pedicels 0.5-2 mm; sepals concave, all dorsally pubescent, 5-6 mm long, acute to acuminate. [
<bibRefCitation id="E91F16D1AB10DE1F8DFFFE5BDF901837" author="Petrov, VA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique" pageId="208" pageNumber="209" pagination="132 - 150" refId="B265" refString="Petrov, VA, 1935. Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium. Bulletin de la Societe de Naturalistes de Moscou, Section Biologique 44: 132 - 150" title="Revisio critica specierum Convolvuli generis in viciniis florae USSR sponte nascentium." volume="44" year="1935">Petrov 1935</bibRefCitation>
: 134 (plate)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5BEE30CEDBCBF6D576973DBA3000BB55" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A8DD3958226A941D7FA8D1C588DF03ED" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB080FAAB7132629DA256A9284068AB7" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">
China: Kashgar (
<emphasis id="A9A8A030DD1C01516AA6C3E572653DDB" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Popov</emphasis>
241, 614); Kazakstan (
<emphasis id="366A806C2C313697A9BD7BD26017BF0E" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Goloskokov</emphasis>
s.n. [29/6/1971], 
<emphasis id="BCD81D1419B588D8FC48B6375B810AB5" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Divnogorski</emphasis>
s.n. [24/5/1907], 
<emphasis id="2EC1DC717CA018AC7CE0C5B1DBE949B4" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Shishkin</emphasis>
s.n. [17/7/1935], 
<emphasis id="05D60E400C4FCA507FA2BDF68E1B6D04" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Ptaschicki</emphasis>
632, 642); Kyrgyzstan (
<emphasis id="E6EFA1B8A91ABA4031F8A6C840055725" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Abolin</emphasis>
712, 
<emphasis id="8FA5615D93A14E54982201DD1E68E507" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Dessiatoff</emphasis>
1864); sin loc. (
<emphasis id="5B39E3CB961B9278D2A77971FA0D1D0A" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Chaffanjon</emphasis>
158).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="97F377AA892B995905E5D866D4052824" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1A7510638BF98AAC7667E01C82F57E56" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8A8A058BD8CE1D66CD02B75DD7DDCF3" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName id="58FD1E16F1F9E6C357736683AF35A8D5" authorityName="Popov, Trudy Turkestansk. Gosud. Univ. 4: 56, pl. between 64 - 65. 1922. (Popov" authorityYear="1922" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus spinifer" order="Solanales" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spinifer">
<emphasis id="1A3F5CB743B4211F3C60119B78193276" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convolvulus spinifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears to be somewhat intermediate between 
<taxonomicName id="DB15BCB39F8BDD971EF890428B614A11" authorityName="Regel &amp; Schmahl., Trudy Imp. S. - Peterburgsk. Bot. Sada 6: 339. 1879. (Regel" authorityYear="1879" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus krauseanus" order="Solanales" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="krauseanus">
<emphasis id="A21523DEFD1A974B5817C7961549C00D" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convolvulus krauseanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A4F3E3C69AFA4B30B8529C6524C4976E" authorityName="Turcz., Bull. Soc. Imp. Naturalistes Moscou 5: 201. 1832. (Turczaninow" authorityYear="1832" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus tragacanthoides" order="Solanales" pageId="154" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tragacanthoides">
<emphasis id="DC9A97E6B8FE4B1469539958B4088E3C" italics="true" pageId="154" pageNumber="155">Convolvulus tragacanthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
